body_html: @kemusa I think you may try to determine whether your program really use the library you have just built and the file which contains the op CountExtremelyRandomStats was exactly built in that library. The reason I add 2 lines in that BUILD file is I find the file /tensorflow/tensorflow/contrib/tensor_forest/kernels/count_extremely_random_stats_op.cc will be built by the rule cc_library[name=v2_ops](/tensorflow/tensorflow/contrib/tensor_forest/BUILD). And it will eventually be built by the two lines I add in /tensorflow/tensorflow/BUILD.

body: @kemusa I think you may try to determine whether your program really use the library you have just built and the file which contains the op `CountExtremelyRandomStats` was exactly built in that library. The reason I add 2 lines in that BUILD file is I find the file `/tensorflow/tensorflow/contrib/tensor_forest/kernels/count_extremely_random_stats_op.cc` will be built by the rule `cc_library[name=v2_ops]`(`/tensorflow/tensorflow/contrib/tensor_forest/BUILD`). And it will eventually be built by the two lines I add in `/tensorflow/tensorflow/BUILD`.
